flowRoot.flowPara: When you are dealt a Damage card, you may immediately discard that card and recover 1 shield.
Then, discard this Upgrade card.
After you perform an attack that does not hit, you may immediately perform a primary weapon attack. You may change 1 f result to a d result. You cannot perform another attack this round.
You may treat all 8 maneuvers as green maneuvers.
Once per round, before you roll 1 or more defense dice, you may guess aloud a number of e results. If you roll that many e results (before modifying dice), add 1 e result.
When attacking, if you have a target lock on the defender, you may spend that target lock to change all of your f results to d results.
At the start of the Activation phase, you may discard this card to allow all friendly ships that reveal a red maneuver to treat that maneuver as a white maneuver until the end of the phase .
At the end of the End phase, if you have no shields, you may recover 1 shield and roll 1 attack die. On a d result, randomly flip 1 of your facedown Damage cards faceup and resolve it.
Once per round, when a friendly ship at Range 1-3 performs a focus action or would be assigned a focus token, you may assign that ship an evade token instead.
After you remove a stress token from your ship, you may assign a focus token to your ship.
ACTION: Roll 2 defense dice. For each f result, assign 1 focus token to your ship. For each e result, assign 1 evade token to your ship.
You may perform attacks while overlapping an obstacle.
Your attacks cannot be obstructed.
ACTION: Perform a free boost action. Then receive 1 ion token.
You may maintain 2 target locks (only 1 per enemy ship).
When you acquire a target lock, you may lock onto 2 different ships.
When you reveal a maneuver, you may rotate your dial to another maneuver with the same bearing.
You cannot rotate to a red maneuver if you have any stress tokens.
After you perform an attack against a ship inside your firing arc at Range 2, that ship receives 1 stress token.
You may maintain 2 target locks (only 1 per enemy ship).
When you acquire a target lock, you may lock onto 2 different ships.
